A Klawer man arrested for murdering a 13-year-old boy remains behind bars after appearing in court this morning. The tragedy has caused outrage amongst the community of Klawer. eNCA reporter Ronald Masinda has more. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - A Klawer man arrested for murdering a 13-year-old boy remains behind bars after appearing in court on Monday morning. The suspect is said to have confessed to murdering the boy. READ: Klawer murder-accused to appear in court Body parts were found in his property in a drain pipe. The tragedy has caused outrage amongst the community of Klawer. READ: Distraught Klawer mother wants answers Communities are concerned about the heinous violence and accuse the police of inaction. Several people are protesting outside the police station.